text: Katchalski may refer to: *Aharon Katzir-Katchalsky, or Aharon Katzir (1914–1972), Israeli pioneer in the study of the electrochemistry of biopolymers **Katchalsky (crater), a crater that lies on the far side of the Moon, and is named after scientist Aharon Katzir-Katchalsky **Katchalski- Katzir algorithm, algorithm for docking of rigid molecules, developed by Ephraim Katchalski/Katzir
title: Katchalski
